## 1. Global Standards
- Follow best practices for code structure and organization.
- Prioritize readability over raw performance.
- Use DRY (Don't Repeat Yourself) principles.
- Ensure all code is complete, tested, and production-ready.
- Avoid TODOs and unfinished features.
- Provide meaningful comments and documentation.
- Implement accessibility (WCAG 2.1) and security best practices.
- Follow a consistent file/folder structure.
- Maintain clear separation of concerns.
- Use strict TypeScript configurations and avoid using 'any' type.